";Lumpen Left is a critique of the PKK, arguing that the organization lacks any real connection to leftist ideologies. It is sustained by populism rather than a commitment to human or workers' rights. The book provides a step-by-step account of the PKK's origins. The opening pages describe the rise of fascism in Turkey in the 1970s, detailing how leftist groups were massacred with US support, and how the PKK was founded during this era. Finally, the book explains why the PKK is designated as a terrorist organization in Turkey, arguing that it serves its own interests rather than those of the Kurdish people;
Handmade Websites as Punk Zines;Insa Deist & Hjördis Lyn Behncken;Florian Meisner;Kies;;WWW;;„Auf der Suche“ befasst sich mit Gefühlen im Zusammenhang mit der Vorstellung einer inneren Gedankenwelt. In einem Raum der Bewegung wird die Suche nach einem Felsen in der Brandung zu einer Metapher für die Suche nach Stabilität in einer unvorhersehbaren Welt.;“On the Search” considers feelings in relation to the notion of an inner landscape. In a space of movement, the search for a rock in the surf becomes a metaphor for the search for stability in an unpredictable world.;
